children.subject: Yes. RL was pretty interesting so I went through the 188 course previously on my own and also read through online sources. So instead of taking 188 which would just redo RL and machine learning for a large part, I decided to do 285 since it seems super interesting and relevant to the field I want to work in.
Wait how are you taking CS285 without CS188? Did you self-learn RL???

history.content: I am currently enrolled in CS188 but was also admitted to CS285. After receiving the enrollment code, I tried swapping CS188 with CS285 but was put on the waitlist for CS285. Since I am confirmed for CS285, I know I will be admitted into the course but am not sure when. When I get into CS285, CS188 will also be dropped automatically. The add/drop deadline without fees is this Friday. If I get enrolled in CS285 after this Friday, will I be charged the add/drop fee because I am already trying to switch into the course which I should be able to but due to administrative delays, I am not allowed to yet?
history.subject: Drop Deadline
